      "content": "Alternative approaches like living constitutionalism are not merely academic exercises; they are a deliberate strategy to allow the Constitution to adapt to changing social values, which critics argue is necessary for justice in a modern democracy. While some defenders of originalism claim these methods lead to judicial overreach, others argue that a static text becomes unworkable when it contradicts the fundamental rights of contemporary citizens. Ultimately, the debate often boils down to whether the Supreme Court should act as a historical archive or a dynamic guardian of evolving liberty.",
